<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Kornada</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Hail all!  I am a beginning shaman and would like to know opinions on 1h blunt vs 2h blunt.  I seem drawn to 2h blunt, but really don't know the pros and cons of each.  I'm assuming both have each.  Any help would be greatly appreciated!<P>Kornada</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">teflonlop</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">train em both, definatly. I use a worn great staff during the day and at night I use my cracked staff witha  large lantern. Later when you have a larger choice of weapons you'll want to have some skill in each.<P>tef<BR>fickle 10th lvl rogue on rallos zek<BR>teff 8th lvl bard on rallos zek<BR>craithir 4th lvl shaman on rallos zek</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Roces</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Id definatley go with 2hb, try to get someone to donate a spare 2hb weapon...they're not too hard to find usually, but your definatley going to want the 2hb in the long run, me and my gwc are doing just fine now  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/smile.gif"><P>Bianca, shaman of the 17th level<BR>Tunare</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Wilu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">to begin with 2HB as you can very quickly do the Bloodforge Hammer quest (Take Tumpys head  (from the Fish inn at queynos) to Byzor Bloodforge in Kaladim) a weapon which will last you until lv20 easily.<BR>The hammer itself is 13Dam 50Delay +10 SV vs Magic and it acts a s a lightsource pretty damn good for a shaman.<P>You will want to try to keep up your 1HB too thogh as later on you start to lay off on the melee and want to carry a shield for extra protection or a mana/stat boosting item in your shield hand.<P>Piercing isnt really an option as theres no great weapons for shaman (aprt from a trident I cant remember the name of)<P>------------------<BR>Sister of the 14th Season <BR>Arcanum Magus<BR>Veeshan<P><A HREF="http://www.arcanum-magus.org" TARGET=_blank>www.arcanum-magus.org</A> <P><p>[This message has been edited by Wilu (edited 12-02-1999).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
